                             [hrule.gif]

                             JGI Instrumentation

                             [hrule.gif]

   The following are the major pieces of equipment currently in use in the
   Joint Genome Institute for production sequencing or mapping.


     Sequencing Instrumentation
       * Molecular Dynamics MegaBACE

     Liquid Handling Instruments
       * Thermo Labsystems Multidrop Dispensers
       * Robbins Hydra
       * BioRobotics BioFill
       * Biotek ELX 405 Plate washer
       * Beckman Multimek

     Colony Picking
       * Genomic Solutions Flexys w/autoloader
       * BioRobotics BioPick
       * Genemachines Gel-2-Well
       * Genetix Q-Pix

     Thermal Cycling
       * MJ Research Thermal Cycler (96 & 384 alpha units)
       * Perkin-Elmer 9600 & 9700 PCR Machines

     Robotics Systems
       * CRS Robotics Systems
       * Beckman Biomek FX
       * CCS/Packard Minitrack
       * Tecan Genesis 150 & 200
       * Packard Multiprobe
       * LBNL PrepTrack I & II

     Additional Equipment
       * Agarose Gel Analysis System
       * Genemachines HydroShear
       * Genemachines HiGro Oxygenated Incubators
       * BioRad Fluor-S Imaging Station
       * Centrifuges - Beckman, Eppendorf, Sorvall, Savant


